end.Willingness to travel up to 20% for in-person client meetings and industry conferences\n\nFirst-Month Focus\n\nMaster Sully’s product, understand our client’s clinical workflows, and build a point of view on “what winning looks like” for each strategic account.Establish executive cadence: stakeholder map, success metrics, meeting rhythm, and a success plan for each of your accountsDeliver at least one visible client win (adoption lift, workflow unlock, expansion path)\n\nWhy Join Sully.ai?\n\n🔥 Revolutionizing the antiquated $800B+ Healthcare market\n\n🧠 60%+ Ex-founders who have built, scaled, exited. We hire A-players\n\n⚡️ Speed matters: we operate with urgency, autonomy, and ownership\n\n🧪 You’ll work on real, first-of-their-kind problems at the edge of AI and medicine\n\n❤️ Your work directly unlocks doctors to reclaim their time, and patients get better, faster care\n\nSully.ai is an equal opportunity employer. In addition to EEO being the law, it is a policy that is fully consistent with our principles. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to status as a protected veteran or a qualified individual with a disability, or other protected status such as race, religion, color, national origin, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, genetic information, pregnancy or age. Sully.ai prohibits any form of workplace harassment."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4406990437","title":"Sales Account Executive","company":"Burjline Builders","location":"Dubai","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.burjlinebuilders.com/jobs/7653955-sales-account-executive","description":"Job Title: Sales Account Executive\n\nCompany: Qureos\n\nEmployment Type: Full-Time\n\nJob Overview\n\nQureos is revolutionising the way young people learn and work by offering job matching, one-on-one mentorships, and hands-on projects across in-demand fields. We are seeking a dynamic and experienced Sales Account Executive to join our team and drive our commercial growth. The ideal candidate will be a strategic leader with a proven track record in sales, responsible for developing and executing sales strategies, leading a high-performing team, and building strong relationships with key clients and partners. This is an excellent opportunity to make a significant impact within a mission-driven company that is shaping the future of early-career talent.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n Develop and implement a comprehensive sales strategy to achieve company sales targets and expand our customer base. Lead, mentor, and manage the sales team, fostering a culture of success and ongoing development. Identify and pursue new business opportunities with corporate partners, educational institutions, and other relevant organisations. Build and maintain strong, long-lasting relationships with key clients, understanding their needs and ensuring their satisfaction. Oversee the entire sales cycle from lead generation to closing, ensuring a professional and efficient process. Analyse sales data and market trends to provide accurate forecasting and inform strategic decisions. Collaborate closely with the marketing and product development teams to ensure our services are aligned with market demands. Represent Qureos at industry events and conferences to build brand awareness and network with potential clients.\n\nQualifications\n\n Proven work experience as a Sales Account Executive or in a similar senior sales role, preferably within the EdTech, HR Tech, or recruitment industry. A demonstrable track record of achieving and exceeding sales targets. Excellent leadership and team management skills with the ability to inspire and motivate a team. Strong business acumen and strategic thinking abilities. Exceptional communication, negotiation, and interpersonal skills. Proficiency in CRM software and sales analytics tools. A genuine passion for Qureos's mission to empower young professionals. A bachelor's degree in Business Administration, Marketing, or a related field is preferred.\n\nBenefits\n\n A competitive salary and performance-based commission structure. The opportunity to be a key part of a fast-growing, innovative company making a positive impact. A collaborative, supportive, and forward-thinking work environment. Significant opportunities for professional growth and career advancement. Flexible working arrangements to support a healthy work-life balance."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4408258707","title":"Head of Operations UAE","company":"BTSE","location":"Victoria","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.lever.co/BTSE/210f5cb6-ccc1-4185-9b2c-19cac1333717/?source=LinkedIn&lever-source=LinkedIn","description":"BTSE Group is a global leader in fintech and blockchain technology, anchored by three core business pillars: Exchange, Payments, and Infrastructure Development. Serving over 100 corporate clients worldwide, we provide white-label exchange and payment solutions. Our offerings encompass everything from exchange infrastructure hosting and development to custody, wallets, payments, blockchain integration, trading, and more.\n\nBTSE has pioneered multiple trading technologies that have been widely adopted across the industry, establishing new benchmarks for innovation, performance, and security in digital asset trading. Consistently ranked among the top 10 global exchanges, BTSE is expanding rapidly and invites ambitious, driven professionals to become valuable members of its B2C and B2B businesses.\n\nAbout The Opportunity\n\nWe are seeking a Head of Operations to lead the Dubai entity’s operations. This role will oversee day-to-day activities, establish operational frameworks, and support regulatory compliance and licensing.\n\nThe successful candidate must meet VARA's fit and proper standards, including demonstrated integrity, relevant industry experience, an understanding of the virtual asset regulatory framework, and financial soundness\n\nResponsibilities\n\n Oversee daily operations across trading, payments, and client lifecycle.  Establish and maintain operational processes, controls, and monitoring frameworks.  Support licensing and act as a key point of contact for regulators, including VARA.  Ensure alignment with compliance, risk, and internal policies.  Identify and manage operational risks, including incident handling and escalation.  Collaborate with global teams and provide r